{"schema": {"fields":[{"type":"integer","name":"index"},{"type":"string","name":"author_association"},{"type":"string","name":"body"},{"type":"datetime","name":"created_at"},{"type":"string","name":"html_url"},{"type":"integer","name":"id"},{"type":"string","name":"issue_url"},{"type":"string","name":"node_id"},{"type":"datetime","name":"updated_at"},{"type":"string","name":"url"},{"type":"string","name":"user"}],"pandas_version":"0.20.0","primaryKey":["index"]}, "data": [{"index":0,"author_association":"OWNER","body":"> This could be an html error or an orbital controls error. I will look into it.\r\n\r\nAny findings?","created_at":"2016-12-09T19:29:52.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/9437#issuecomment-266100798","id":266100798,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/9437","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDI2NjEwMDc5OA==","updated_at":"2016-12-09T19:29:52.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/266100798","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars0.githubusercontent.com\/u\/97088?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjk3MDg4","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"mrdoob","type":"User","id":97088,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/orgs"}},{"index":1,"author_association":"COLLABORATOR","body":"I've looked into the issue today and i can only reproduce if the example runs inside an `iFrame`. Without an `iFrame` (https:\/\/threejs.org\/examples\/misc_controls_orbit.html) everything works fine. And i think I know why :blush: \r\n\r\n- Call  https:\/\/threejs.org\/examples\/#misc_controls_orbit and use the arrow keys. Everything works fine so far.\r\n- If you click on the side bar, arrow keys stop working since the inner `window` object (`iFrame`) lost focus. That's the reason why the arrow keys stop working.\r\n- Because the `mousedown` event listener of `OrbitControls` calls `event.preventDefault()`, the inner window never gets focus again even if you click on it.\r\n\r\nI don't think we can provide a reasonable fix for `OrbitControls`. IMO, this problem has to be managed on application level.","created_at":"2018-03-07T13:42:11.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/9437#issuecomment-371141543","id":371141543,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/9437","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDM3MTE0MTU0Mw==","updated_at":"2018-03-07T14:47:29.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/371141543","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Mugen87\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Mugen87\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars2.githubusercontent.com\/u\/12612165?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Mugen87","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Mugen87\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/Mugen87","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Mugen87\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjEyNjEyMTY1","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Mugen87\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Mugen87\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Mugen87\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"Mugen87","type":"User","id":12612165,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Mugen87\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Mugen87\/orgs"}},{"index":2,"author_association":"COLLABORATOR","body":"@Mugen87 Yes, there are too many use cases. Robustness sometimes must be handled at the application level. I think this can be closed.","created_at":"2018-03-07T16:52:03.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/9437#issuecomment-371204252","id":371204252,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/9437","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDM3MTIwNDI1Mg==","updated_at":"2018-03-07T16:52:03.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/371204252","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars2.githubusercontent.com\/u\/1000017?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/WestLangley","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjEwMDAwMTc=","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"WestLangley","type":"User","id":1000017,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/orgs"}},{"index":3,"author_association":"OWNER","body":"How about adding `if ( domElement instanceof HTMLElement ) domElement.focus()` in the `onMouseDown` function?","created_at":"2018-03-08T01:19:26.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/9437#issuecomment-371344278","id":371344278,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/9437","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDM3MTM0NDI3OA==","updated_at":"2018-03-08T01:19:26.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/371344278","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars0.githubusercontent.com\/u\/97088?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjk3MDg4","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"mrdoob","type":"User","id":97088,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/orgs"}},{"index":4,"author_association":"COLLABORATOR","body":"Um, does not seem to have any effect. If i change the code to `window.focus();` instead, arrow navigation works again. I guess it's because the `keydown` event listener is attached to `window` and not `canvas`.\r\n\r\nIndependently, this code would only solve the problem partially. If the users clicks outside the `iFrame`, arrow keys won't work after all. I'm not sure it makes sense to fix this in `OrbitControls`.","created_at":"2018-03-08T10:21:58.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/9437#issuecomment-371445285","id":371445285,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/9437","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDM3MTQ0NTI4NQ==","updated_at":"2018-03-08T10:21:58.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/371445285","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Mugen87\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Mugen87\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars2.githubusercontent.com\/u\/12612165?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Mugen87","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Mugen87\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/Mugen87","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Mugen87\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjEyNjEyMTY1","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Mugen87\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Mugen87\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Mugen87\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"Mugen87","type":"User","id":12612165,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Mugen87\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Mugen87\/orgs"}},{"index":5,"author_association":"NONE","body":"Any update on this issue ??","created_at":"2018-09-30T18:29:31.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/9437#issuecomment-425741031","id":425741031,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/9437","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDQyNTc0MTAzMQ==","updated_at":"2018-09-30T18:29:31.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/425741031","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mshamaseen\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mshamaseen\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars1.githubusercontent.com\/u\/38951661?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mshamaseen","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mshamaseen\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mshamaseen","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mshamaseen\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjM4OTUxNjYx","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mshamaseen\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mshamaseen\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mshamaseen\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"mshamaseen","type":"User","id":38951661,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mshamaseen\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mshamaseen\/orgs"}},{"index":6,"author_association":"NONE","body":"Ok i found a work around in a forum:\r\n\r\n> Problem solved. My issue ended up being two pronged:\r\n> \r\n>     I was triggering a browser security exception by using the absolute path to my website in the iframe (<iframe src=\"http:\/\/www.mysite.com\/dir\/index.html\"><\/iframe> instead of the path relative from the domain root <iframe src=\"\/dir\/index.html\"><\/iframe>\r\n>     The other issue was the window variable that inputs were bound to needed to be set to the parent window when one was available (which there is in the case of an iframe). This small snippet fixed that\r\n> \r\n> var realWindow = window.parent || window;\/\/.....  \/\/Attach event listeners  realWindow.addEventListener(    \"keydown\", key.downHandler.bind(key), false  );  realWindow.addEventListener(    \"keyup\", key.upHandler.bind(key), false  );\r\n\r\n","created_at":"2018-09-30T19:57:53.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/9437#issuecomment-425747188","id":425747188,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/9437","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDQyNTc0NzE4OA==","updated_at":"2018-09-30T19:57:53.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/425747188","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mshamaseen\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mshamaseen\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars1.githubusercontent.com\/u\/38951661?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mshamaseen","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mshamaseen\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mshamaseen","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mshamaseen\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjM4OTUxNjYx","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mshamaseen\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mshamaseen\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mshamaseen\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"mshamaseen","type":"User","id":38951661,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mshamaseen\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mshamaseen\/orgs"}},{"index":7,"author_association":"NONE","body":"@mrdoob ok I think I found a solution, in orbitControls line 939 ( in my case) change \r\n\r\n`window.addEventListener( 'keydown', onKeyDown, false ); `\r\n\r\nto:\r\n\r\n```\r\nvar realWindow = window.parent || window;\r\n\r\nrealWindow.addEventListener( 'keydown', onKeyDown, false );\r\n```\r\n\r\nThis will make sure the event is assigned to the right window.","created_at":"2018-09-30T21:07:03.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/9437#issuecomment-425752143","id":425752143,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/9437","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDQyNTc1MjE0Mw==","updated_at":"2018-09-30T21:07:03.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/425752143","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mshamaseen\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mshamaseen\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars1.githubusercontent.com\/u\/38951661?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mshamaseen","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mshamaseen\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mshamaseen","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mshamaseen\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjM4OTUxNjYx","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mshamaseen\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mshamaseen\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mshamaseen\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"mshamaseen","type":"User","id":38951661,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mshamaseen\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mshamaseen\/orgs"}},{"index":8,"author_association":"NONE","body":"@mrdoob In my project I added these codes also in onMouseDown function in orbitControls.js:\r\n\r\n```\r\nrealDocument = parent.document || document;\r\nrealDocument.activeElement.blur();\r\n```\r\n\r\nbecause I have DOM input elements in the same iframe, if I change the focusing (using jquery) to input element, i can't get back to focusing the canvas element using mouse click, so this edit solve the issue.","created_at":"2018-10-02T09:08:47.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/9437#issuecomment-426203385","id":426203385,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/9437","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDQyNjIwMzM4NQ==","updated_at":"2018-10-02T09:08:47.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/426203385","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mshamaseen\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mshamaseen\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars1.githubusercontent.com\/u\/38951661?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mshamaseen","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mshamaseen\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mshamaseen","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mshamaseen\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjM4OTUxNjYx","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mshamaseen\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mshamaseen\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mshamaseen\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"mshamaseen","type":"User","id":38951661,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mshamaseen\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mshamaseen\/orgs"}},{"index":9,"author_association":"CONTRIBUTOR","body":"> keydown event listener is attached to window and not canvas.\r\n\r\nI found this a bit problematic when using OrbitControls inside bigger applications, multiple viewports etc. Here I would suggest to add keyboard listeners on canvas instead.\r\n\r\nHowever, it would also be necessary to enable focus on the canvas (to capture key events) and potentially adjust style for outline if you don't like how focused elements look by default.\r\n\r\nAlso considering #9435 I think all controls should have configurable keys to enable better compatibility with other tools like keyboard selection controls in this particular example.\r\n\r\nTo take it even further (sorry I don't mean to derail this discussion)... I think keyboard commands like \"focus selected\" should live in a separate controller outside OrbitControls.","created_at":"2018-10-02T12:19:18.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/9437#issuecomment-426251820","id":426251820,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/9437","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDQyNjI1MTgyMA==","updated_at":"2018-10-02T12:20:10.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/426251820","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/arodic\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/arodic\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars1.githubusercontent.com\/u\/708984?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/arodic","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/arodic\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/arodic","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/arodic\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjcwODk4NA==","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/arodic\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/arodic\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/arodic\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"arodic","type":"User","id":708984,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/arodic\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/arodic\/orgs"}}]}